The paper describes the development of a deep learning-based system for automatic 3D cephalometric annotation, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a popular ML technique used in CV, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the development of a new system, which involves the use of strategies to implement the system, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves the use of image data resampling, which is a technique used in multimedia (MM) processing, making cs.MM another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of measurement results, which is related to graphics (GR), making it another possible category.
